defs.name: centroid
defs.docs: Calculate the centroid of a `Geometry`.

defs.name: Centroid
defs.docs:
Calculation of the centroid.
 The centroid is the arithmetic mean position of all points in the shape.
 Informally, it is the point at which a cutout of the shape could be perfectly
 balanced on the tip of a pin.
 The geometric centroid of a convex object always lies in the object.
 A non-convex object might have a centroid that _is outside the object itself_.

defs.docs: exterior ring is oriented clockwise, interior rings are oriented counter-clockwise

defs.name: Direction
defs.docs:
By default, a properly-oriented Polygon has its outer ring oriented counter-clockwise,
 and its inner ring(s) oriented clockwise. Selecting `Reversed` will result in a Polygon
 with a clockwise-oriented exterior ring, and counter-clockwise interior ring(s)
